metadata.name: Life, Death, and I
metadata.description:
I see the breath 
Wasted on fear 
For death on the planet, 
I see the life that they sell 
And labels that tell 
That mirrors are  organic, 
So as I toke I laugh at you 
as if you were a joke,
Cause in life or death 
I can even see you with 
I behind the smoke.
